<title>GERMANY: Kloeckner unit sale to cut debt.</title>
<headline>Kloeckner unit sale to cut debt.</headline>
<dateline>BONN 1996-11-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Kloeckner-Werke AG, the German engineering group, said on Thursday the sale of its Kautex-Werke unit will slash the company's debt by 30 percent.</p>
<p>The company said the 468 million mark sale to Textron Inc of the United States would also double Kloeckner's equity-to-assets ratio.</p>
<p>-- William Boston, Bonn Newsroom, 49 228 26097150</p>
